"title": "1352: covenant, the new",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1352",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The fulfilment of God's purposes of salvation expressed in the covenants of the OT, mediated by Jesus Christ and sealed in his blood. It is a covenant of grace, the benefits of which include forgiveness, a renewed relationship with God and, through the Holy Spirit, an inward transformation that enables obedience to its demands and so ensures that it will not again be broken.\n <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:31\">JER 31:31</a></strong> <em>The “new” covenant is contrasted with the covenant made at Sinai which is sometimes referred to as the “old” or “first” covenant.</em></p>\n<h2>The new covenant fulfils the OT covenants</h2>\n<h3>God's covenant with Noah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:9-Isa54:10\">ISA 54:9–54:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:18\">HOS 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant with Abraham</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:72-Luke1:73\">LUK 1:72–1:73</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:25-Acts3:26\">ACT 3:25–3:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14-Gal3:16\">GAL 3:14–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant at Sinai</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:60\">EZK 16:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:62\">EZK 16:62</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:37\">EZK 20:37</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant with David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:3\">ISA 55:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:24-Ezek34:26\">EZK 34:24–34:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:25-Ezek37:26\">EZK 37:25–37:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:69\">LUK 1:69</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ, the mediator of the new covenant</h2>\n<h3>The new covenant fulfilled in the Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:1\">MAL 3:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:6\">ISA 42:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:8\">ISA 49:8</a></p>\n<h3>The new covenant effected through Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:16-Heb9:17\">HEB 9:16–9:17</a></p>\n<h3>The new covenant sealed in Jesus Christ's blood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:24\">MRK 14:24</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:8\">EXO 24:8</a> <em>Blood was an important element in sealing the Sinaitic covenant</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:54\">JHN 6:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:29\">HEB 10:29</a></p>\n<h2>The ministry of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:6\">2CO 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:21\">ISA 59:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26-Ezek36:27\">EZK 36:26–36:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:2-Rom8:4\">ROM 8:2–8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:8\">2CO 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>The superior blessings of the new covenant</h2>\n<h3>God's grace and mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a></strong> <em>The blood of Abel cried out to God for justice and retribution; the blood of Jesus Christ, shed to seal the new covenant, cries out for mercy and forgiveness.</em></p>\n<h3>A complete forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:12\">HEB 8:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:34\">JER 31:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:27\">ROM 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:17\">HEB 10:17</a></p>\n<h3>Release from the law's condemnation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:9\">2CO 3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13-Gal3:14\">GAL 3:13–3:14</a></p>\n<h3>An inward enabling to obey God's laws</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32-Jer31:33\">JER 31:32–31:33</a></strong> <em>The old covenant was broken because its demands were not met. Under the new covenant the requirements of obedience are not abolished, but in writing his laws on human hearts, God gives the ability to meet the covenant demands.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:38-Jer32:40\">JER 32:38–32:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:19-Ezek11:20\">EZK 11:19–11:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:3\">2CO 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:9-Heb8:10\">HEB 8:9–8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:16\">HEB 10:16</a></p>\n<h3>A new knowledge of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:11\">HEB 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:34\">JER 31:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:15-2Cor3:16\">2CO 3:15–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>A renewed relationship with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:26-Ezek37:27\">EZK 37:26–37:27</a></strong> <em>“peace” refers to spiritual and material well-being; real peace is possible only for those in a right relationship with God. The formula “I will be their God, and they will be my people” is associated also with the Abrahamic and especially the Sinaitic covenants.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:7\">JER 24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:1\">JER 31:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:30-Ezek34:31\">EZK 34:30–34:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:19-Hos2:23\">HOS 2:19–2:23</a></p>\n<h3>A superior priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:6\">HEB 8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:22\">HEB 7:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24-Heb9:25\">HEB 9:24–9:25</a></p>\n<h3>A superior sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:20-Heb9:23\">HEB 9:20–9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:26-Heb9:28\">HEB 9:26–9:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:4\">HEB 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:8-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:8–10:14</a></p>\n<h3>A lasting covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:8\">ISA 61:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:11\">2CO 3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:5\">JER 50:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:7\">HEB 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:13\">HEB 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20\">HEB 13:20</a></p>",
